This car, while stationary, may influence the available driving space for the ego vehicle, posing a consideration for navigational adjustments. Secondly, among other objects, there are large spools and a trash bin located on the sidewalk to the right of the road. Although these items are not directly on the road, their presence could potentially lead to obstacles if they were to accidentally roll or be moved into the driving path. This scenario underscores the importance of being alert to both on-road and off-road elements that could impact driving decisions and safety.
